.env
# .claude/ holds Claude Code config + session state. Keep most of it
# user-local (per-machine session history, local overrides), but
# track shared team artifacts: slash commands under commands/, the
# baseline permission allowlist in settings.json, and the skill
# discovery symlinks under skills/ that point Claude at canonical
# SKILL.md files in ai/skills/.
#
# Pattern note: ignore immediate children of .claude/ via `*` rather
# than the directory itself, so the negations can re-include
# specific subpaths. `.claude/` would have ignored the whole tree
# and made `!.claude/commands/` unreachable per gitignore semantics.
.claude/*
!.claude/commands/
!.claude/skills/
!.claude/settings.json
# Default GATEWAY_DATA_DIR for local dev. Holds the auto-generated
# bootstrap file (AES-GCM control-plane key + admin bearer token, mode
# 0600). Never commit it.
.data/
.gocache/
.gomodcache/
.gopath/
# Built binary produced by `make build`. Anchored to the repo root so a
# package or test happening to be named "gateway" elsewhere isn't ignored.
/gateway
node_modules/
ui/node_modules/
e2e/local-ollama-*.log
ui/dist/*
!ui/dist/.gitkeep
ui/*.tsbuildinfo
ui/test-results/
ui/playwright-report/
ui/coverage/
coverage.out
# Goreleaser output. Snapshot and release runs both write into ./dist
# at repo root and `--clean` deletes anything in there — so nothing
# under dist/ should ever be tracked, otherwise goreleaser hits "git
# is in a dirty state" the next time it cleans. Anchored with leading
# / so the rule doesn't shadow ui/dist/ (which has its own block above).
/dist/

# Tauri desktop app build artifacts.
tauri/node_modules/
# Rust build output (target/) is large and fully reproducible.
tauri/src-tauri/target/
# The sidecar binary is copied into binaries/ by make tauri-sidecar;
# it is platform-specific and built on demand — not tracked.
tauri/src-tauri/binaries/hecate*
!tauri/src-tauri/binaries/.gitkeep
